question: 航空母艦
sourceMnemonic: An <kanji>aviation</kanji> (<ja>航空</ja>) <kanji>mother</kanji> <kanji>warship</kanji> is a warship that is like mother to all the aviation things (the airplanes). They come home to their mother warship, which is an <vocabulary>aircraft carrier</vocabulary>.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word that uses the on'yomi readings of the kanji. You should be able to read this on your own.
